This checks out. Closest theoretical approaches:<p><pre><code>    >>> &quot;%e&quot; % (Pluto.orbit.periapsis - Earth.orbit.apoapsis)
    &#x27;4.272109e+12&#x27;
    >>> &quot;%e&quot; % (Mars.orbit.periapsis - Earth.orbit.apoapsis)
    &#x27;5.455552e+10&#x27;
    >>> &quot;%e&quot; % (Moon.orbit.periapsis)
    &#x27;3.631042e+08&#x27;
    >>> &quot;%e&quot; % Earth.radius
    &#x27;6.371000e+06&#x27;
</code></pre>
Earth-Pluto: 4.27 Tm = 4.27e9 km = 2.65e9 miles<p>Earth-Mars: 54.6 Gm = 54.6e6 km = 33.9e6 miles<p>Earth-Moon: 363 Mm = 363e3 km = 226e3 miles<p>Earth radius: 6.37 Mm = 6.37e3 km = 3.96e3 miles
